-- Czech Government Proposes 32% Tax on Carbon Credits in 2011-12
-- B y   L a d k a   B a u e r o v a
-- 2010-11-02T11:07:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-02/czech-government-proposes-32-tax-on-carbon-credits-in-2011-12.html
The Czech government is proposing a
32 percent tax on carbon dioxide allowances awarded to power
producers in 2011 and 2012 as a way to limit the impact of solar
energy boom on electricity prices next year, Finance Ministry
spokeswoman Alzbeta Plivova said today.  The proposal may be discussed this or next week, she said
in a telephone interview. The proceeds will be sued to cap
electricity prices next year which as set to rise due to
generous feed-in tariffs for solar energy producers.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ladka Bauerova at 
 lbauerova@bloomberg.net  